       PROCEDURE DIVISION.
       MAIN-LOGIC SECTION.
           OPEN INPUT INFILE
                OUTPUT OUTFILE.

           PERFORM READ-LOOP UNTIL EOF = 'Y'

           PERFORM BUILD-PAIN-STRUCTURE
           PERFORM GENERATE-AND-WRITE-XML

           CLOSE INFILE OUTFILE
           GOBACK
           .
           EXIT.

       READ-LOOP SECTION.
           READ INFILE
               AT END MOVE 'Y' TO EOF
               NOT AT END
                 ADD 1 TO WS-COUNT
                 PERFORM LOAD-TX-FROM-REC
           END-READ
           .
           EXIT.

       LOAD-TX-FROM-REC SECTION.
      * Amount as cents (13 digits) -> decimal string with '.'
      * Convert to unsigned integer, then produce 2 decimal places
      * Move EndToEndId (left-trim spaces)
           MOVE FUNCTION TRIM(IR-END2END) TO TX-END2END(WS-COUNT)

      * Build decimal amount: integer part and fractional part
           IF IR-AMOUNT-CENTS IS NUMERIC
           THEN
              MOVE IR-AMOUNT-CENTS TO WS-CNTRL-SUM-CENTS
              ADD  IR-AMOUNT-CENTS TO WS-CNTRL-SUM-CENTS
           END-IF

           PERFORM VARYING OUT-LEN FROM 1 BY 1 UNTIL OUT-LEN > 1
              EXIT PERFORM
           END-PERFORM

      * Compute amount string XX...X.XX
      *    CALL 'CEEDIV' USING IR-AMOUNT-CENTS 100 OMITTED OMITTED

      * Fallback simple formatting (no LE intrinsic available here),
      * so do manual split.
           MOVE IR-AMOUNT-CENTS TO AMT-INT
           DIVIDE AMT-INT BY 100 GIVING AMT-INT REMAINDER AMT-FRAC
           STRING AMT-INT  DELIMITED BY SIZE
                  '.'      DELIMITED BY SIZE
                  AMT-FRAC DELIMITED BY SIZE
                  INTO TX-AMT-DEC(WS-COUNT)
           END-STRING
           IF AMT-FRAC < 10
           THEN
              STRING FUNCTION TRIM(TX-AMT-DEC(WS-COUNT))
                     '0' DELIMITED BY SIZE
                     INTO TX-AMT-DEC(WS-COUNT)
              END-STRING
           END-IF

           MOVE 'EUR'                   TO TX-AMT-CCY(WS-COUNT)
           MOVE FUNCTION TRIM(IR-NAME)  TO TX-CDTR-NAME(WS-COUNT)
           MOVE FUNCTION TRIM(IR-IBAN)  TO TX-CDTR-IBAN(WS-COUNT)
           MOVE 'Remittance'            TO TX-REMIT(WS-COUNT)
           .
           EXIT.

       BUILD-PAIN-STRUCTURE SECTION.
      * Populate the DOCUMENT structure from WS-PARAMS
           ACCEPT WS-DATE FROM DATE YYYYMMDD
           ACCEPT WS-TIME FROM TIME

           MOVE WS-MSG-ID     TO MsgId
           STRING WS-DATE(1:4) '-' WS-DATE(5:2) '-' WS-DATE(7:2)
                   DELIMITED BY SIZE
                  'T'  DELIMITED BY SIZE
                  WS-TIME(1:2) ':' WS-TIME(3:2) ':' WS-TIME(5:2)
                  DELIMITED BY SIZE
                  INTO CreDtTm
           END-STRING
           MOVE WS-COUNT      TO NbOfTxs NbOfTxs2

      *   Control sum in euros with decimal separator '.'
           MOVE WS-CNTRL-SUM-CENTS TO SUM-INT
           DIVIDE SUM-INT BY 100 GIVING SUM-INT REMAINDER SUM-FRAC
           STRING SUM-INT  DELIMITED BY SIZE
                  '.'      DELIMITED BY SIZE
                  SUM-FRAC DELIMITED BY SIZE
                  INTO CtrlSum
           END-STRING
           MOVE CtrlSum TO CtrlSum2

           MOVE WS-INITG-NAME        TO InitgPty Nm OF InitgPty
           MOVE WS-PMTINF-ID         TO PmtInfId
           MOVE 'TRF'                TO PmtMtd
           MOVE 'true'               TO BtchBookg
           MOVE 'SEPA'               TO SvcCode OF SvcLvl
           MOVE WS-REQ-EXEC-DATE     TO ReqdExctnDt
           MOVE WS-DEBTOR-NAME       TO Nm OF Dbtr
           MOVE WS-DEBTOR-IBAN       TO IBAN OF DbtrAcctId OF DbtrAcct
           MOVE WS-CURRENCY          TO Ccy OF DbtrAcct
           MOVE WS-DEBTOR-BIC        TO BIC OF FinInstnId OF DbtrAgt
           MOVE 'SLEV'               TO ChrgBr

           PERFORM VARYING OUT-LEN FROM 1 BY 1 UNTIL OUT-LEN > WS-COUNT
             MOVE TX-END2END(OUT-LEN)
               TO EndToEndId   OF PmtId    OF CdtTrfTxInf(OUT-LEN)
             MOVE TX-END2END(OUT-LEN)
               TO InstrId      OF PmtId    OF CdtTrfTxInf(OUT-LEN)
             MOVE TX-AMT-DEC(OUT-LEN)
               TO InstdAmt     OF Amt      OF CdtTrfTxInf(OUT-LEN)
             MOVE TX-AMT-CCY(OUT-LEN)
               TO InstdAmtCcy  OF Amt      OF CdtTrfTxInf(OUT-LEN)
             MOVE TX-CDTR-NAME(OUT-LEN)
               TO Nm           OF Cdtr     OF CdtTrfTxInf(OUT-LEN)
             MOVE TX-CDTR-IBAN(OUT-LEN)
               TO IBAN OF CdtrAcctId OF CdtrAcct
                                           OF CdtTrfTxInf(OUT-LEN)
             MOVE TX-REMIT(OUT-LEN)
               TO Ustrd        OF RmtInf   OF CdtTrfTxInf(OUT-LEN)
           END-PERFORM
           .
           EXIT.

       GENERATE-AND-WRITE-XML SECTION.
      * Use XML GENERATE to produce UTF-8 encoded XML directly
      * into XML-OUT buffer, then write in chunks to the VB output.
           XML GENERATE XML-OUT
               FROM DOCUMENT
               COUNT IN XML-LEN
               WITH ENCODING 1208
      * ENCODING 1208 = UTF-8 (Unicode Transformation Format - 8-bit)
               WITH XML-DECLARATION
